org.jumprobotics.robot.kinematics

Class ChassisVelocity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jumprobotics.robot.kinematics.ChassisVelocity

  • public class ChassisVelocity
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the velocity of a robot chassis w.r.t. the robot frame of reference.

    In non-holonomic drive bases, the y component of the translational velocity should always be 0 because they cannot move sideways.

    • Method Detail

      • getTranslationalVelocity

        public Vector2 getTranslationalVelocity()
        Gets the translational velocity component of this chassis velocity.

        The x component of the translational velocity is the robot's forward velocity (positive is forwards) and the y component is the sideways velocity (positive is to the left).

        Returns:
        The translational velocity w.r.t. the robot.

      • getAngularVelocity

        public double getAngularVelocity()
        Gets the angular velocity component of this chassis velocity.

        Positive velocities are counter-clockwise movement.

        Returns:
        The angular velocity.
